description: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the Invesco Multi-Factor Income Index (the "underlying index"). The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is an index of other indexes and is comprised of component securities of such indexes (each, a "sub-index"). The underlying index is rebalanced monthly, and the fund will generally rebalance in accordance with the underlying index. It is non-diversified.
name: Invesco Multi-Factor Income ETF
